at the same time as you are.

143
00:15:16,397 --> 00:15:22,347
No, tomorrow's heroine could
be you yourself.

144
00:15:31,557 --> 00:15:33,275
I'm home.

145
00:15:38,637 --> 00:15:41,754
Here we go.
-You're home early.

146
00:15:42,637 --> 00:15:44,992
That's right, I've got to
work at home tonight.

147
00:15:45,717 --> 00:15:50,188
Please heat up your dinner.
The bigger dish is for Shigeto.

148
00:15:50,517 --> 00:15:53,270
Thanks.
-See You on Monday.

149
00:15:53,837 --> 00:15:57,876
My daughters here this weekend.
I've got to go shopping.

150
00:15:58,197 --> 00:16:00,108
That's nice.
Hey Gang.

151
00:16:00,317 --> 00:16:04,435
Please put your washing in the basket.
-Right.

152
00:16:05,477 --> 00:16:07,593
Thanks
-Bye.

153
00:17:58,477 --> 00:18:01,037
Hello.
-It's me.

154
00:18:01,357 --> 00:18:04,588
Yoshikawa. I'm
checking the applications.

155
00:18:04,997 --> 00:18:08,194
They're all good, right?

156
00:18:08,757 --> 00:18:10,987
I don't know what am I
supposed to do?

157
00:18:12,357 --> 00:18:14,825
It's like buying my
first car.

158
00:18:15,837 --> 00:18:18,431
Don't mix your car and wife.

159
00:18:18,677 --> 00:18:22,955
I intend holding the audition
next week. Choose 30 applicants.

160
00:18:23,197 --> 00:18:25,665
30 applicants?
-That's right.

161
00:18:25,837 --> 00:18:30,592
Alright. I'll let you know.
-Don't trust pictures.

162
00:18:31,157 --> 00:18:34,229
Composition can be more useful.
-Understood.

163
00:18:34,397 --> 00:18:36,592
See you.
-Bye.

164
00:18:40,437 --> 00:18:43,668
Choose 30 from all of you?

165
00:18:47,597 --> 00:18:49,394
You're home?

166
00:18:49,557 --> 00:18:53,436
Why don't you knock at
the door? You just arrived?

167
00:18:53,957 --> 00:18:58,826
Yeah. Dinner?
-I'll eat later. Why don't you eat first?

168
00:18:59,077 --> 00:19:00,192
Alright.

169
00:19:00,397 --> 00:19:03,673
I'm having a guest tonight.

170
00:19:04,957 --> 00:19:09,348
Girl friend?
Give her my dinner.

171
00:19:09,837 --> 00:19:10,986
Thank you.

172
00:19:21,677 --> 00:19:23,349
What did I do!

173
00:19:43,317 --> 00:19:45,877
Asami Yamazaki.

174
00:19:56,157 --> 00:19:58,591
Classical Ballet for 12 years.

175
00:20:07,277 --> 00:20:12,397
I'm not sure that I can make an actress of
myself. And you probably won't choose me.

176
00:20:13,157 --> 00:20:15,796
I was simply attracted to this story.

177
00:20:16,917 --> 00:20:22,469
I studied ballet, but damaged
my hips when I was 1 8.

178
00:20:23,837 --> 00:20:28,353
I was devastated as I intended
to practice in London.

179
00:20:29,357 --> 00:20:33,987
Ballet was my priority.
So my dream collapsed.

180
00:20:35,037 --> 00:20:40,236
It might sound exaggerated,
but it's like accepting death.

181
00:20:40,757 --> 00:20:44,352
Living is another way of
reaching death.

182
00:20:44,757 --> 00:20:50,753
I think I know these facts very well.
That's why I applied for this part.

183
00:21:07,917 --> 00:21:11,671
When was this dinosaur living?
-about the latter Cretaceous period.

184
00:21:11,877 --> 00:21:15,995
The later part of Cretaceous
means...

185
00:21:17,837 --> 00:21:19,873
That's a Sauropod right?

186
00:21:20,077 --> 00:21:23,865
Good. What about the dinosaur
that has the Syracuse model.

187
00:21:24,077 --> 00:21:26,466
I don't know.
-Do You want to see?

188
00:21:37,357 --> 00:21:39,587
Hi! Good evening.
-Good evening.

189
00:21:39,797 --> 00:21:41,515
I'm his father.

190
00:21:43,077 --> 00:21:46,865
My name is Misuzu. Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet You too.

191
00:21:47,197 --> 00:21:51,668
I often see her on the train. I thought
she was pretty. Then tried talking to her.

192
00:21:51,877 --> 00:21:53,196
Good job.

193
00:21:54,797 --> 00:21:59,666
I'm interested in biology.
He showed me his books.

194
00:22:00,117 --> 00:22:02,028
We ate your dinner.
-Fine.

195
00:22:02,197 --> 00:22:04,552
Was it his?

196
